    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Devils were given their first day off yesterday since training camp opened 14 days ago, but Turner Stevenson was hospitalized with an infection in his right elbow.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The Devils were given their first day off yesterday since training camp opened 14 days ago, but Turner Stevenson was hospitalized with an infection in his right elbow.</p>
        <p>Stevenson, who cut his elbow in the victory over Pittsburgh last Saturday and played in the loss in Detroit on Sunday, entered St. Barnabas Medical Center in Livingston, N.J., Wednesday night after the cut kept him out of practice for three days and showed no improvement.</p>
        <p>Alex Yannis</p>
        <p>PLUS: HOCKEY</p>
